entry.title: Generate stdlib GN rules from the Rust src tree when rolling Rust
entry.content:
Reland of https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4569316



This avoids the need to:

1. Build gnrt locally

2. Then download the roll CL

3. Copy Rust packages to prod

4. gclient sync

5. Run `gnrt gen --for-std`

6. Reupload the CL



In order to have the Rust roll pass the trybots.



upload_revision.py will, when rolling rust, do the `cargo vendor`

step in the Rust git checkout to get its dependencies, install

cargo and rustc in a sysroot, build `gnrt` using cargo, and then

run `gnrt gen --for-std=third_party/rust_src/src` which regenerates

the GN rules for the Rust stdlib from the updated version of Rust.



Previously gnrt gen --for-std would generate rules from the Rust

library found in //third_party/rust-toolchain, but that requires

Rust to already be rolled, so this now uses the feature of specifying

the Rust source tree root to --for-std.



Bug: 1401042, 1451335

entry.title: Re-enable LaunchingAppThatRequiresNetworkWhilstOfflineShouldShowNetworkScreen
entry.content:
This test flakily failed at the WaitForOobeScreen step, because we jumped straight into the network screen instead of holding on the splash screen for 10 seconds as expected.



The reason we jumped straight into the network screen is the following callpath happening during installation:

NetworkUiController::InitializeNetwork

-> AppLaunchSplashScreenHandler::UpdateAppLaunchState

-> NetworkUiController::OnNetworkStateChanged

-> KioskLaunchController::OnNetworkLost

-> NetworkUiController::OnNetworkLostDuringInstallation

-> NetworkUiController::ShowNetworkConfigureUI.



This was fixed by https://crrev.com/c/4583229 by blocking the call from AppLaunchSplashScreenHandler::UpdateAppLaunchState to NetworkUiController::OnNetworkStateChanged.

entry.title: Use identity scale for filters_scale in RendererPixelTests
entry.content:
The filter scale and origin parameters to the RPDQ are used to directly

define the local matrix the image filters are evaluated with. Using a

default-constructed gfx::Vector2dF has a (0,0) scale factor so the

local matrix is the zero matrix and not invertible.



This went undetected previously because color filters don't have any

geometric parameters affected by the local matrix, so the zero matrix was being silently ignored. A skia-side change is making

`makeWithLocalMatrix()` return null if the matrix is not invertible,

so this updates the tests to use an identity value.

entry.title: [Layout] Fix DCHECK when updating visible tab IDs
entry.content:
Fix a DCHECK in tab_content_manager.cc related to the ThumbnailCacheRefactor [1]. The DCHECK is triggered during

SimpleAnimationLayout if a StaticLayout attempts to invoke

TabContentManager#updateVisibleTabIds while the SimpleAnimationLayout

is active. This happens because StaticLayout updates the visible tab

IDs both when it is shown and when a tab becomes selected (to cover

the scenario where it is already visible). This is incorrect as the

active layout is the only one that should be able to

call updateVisibleTabIds otherwise other layouts might become broken.



Prevent this by filtering Layout#updateCacheVisibleIds{AndPrimary} to

only be called when the StaticLayout is active. Also add an assert to

catch and correct any other instances of this.



This is not a problem for StaticLayout as it updates the visible

tab IDs during show() as well.



Also properly override Layout#setTabModelSelector in StaticLayout. It

is unclear why this was an intentional no-op it does not appear to

cause issues by overriding it and dates back to the great upstreaming in

2015.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:chrome/browser/android/compositor/tab_content_manager.cc;drc=e502291081d7e28f852b0ac8486449d7a1c509e1;l=185

entry.title: [//media][Mac] Eliminate PictureInfo taking in client/service texture ID
entry.content:
VtVideoDecodeAccelerator's PictureInfo struct has two constructors:

- One that is empty and signifies that the accelerator should use

SharedImage

- One that takes in a client/service texture ID and specifies that the

accelerator should *not* use SharedImage



Following the elimination of the NaCL use case and subsequent

refactorings, the codepath that invokes PictureInfo() with a

client/service texture ID is never actually invoked: the client/service

texture ID come from a PictureBuffer instance created by

PictureBufferManager::CreatePictureBuffers(), which now creates only

PictureBuffers with empty client/service texture IDs on Mac. This CL

replaces the codepath that creates a PictureInfo with a client/service

tetxure ID with a CHECK that the PictureBuffer's client/service texture

ID are empty.



A followup CL will eliminate all of the non-SharedImage code in

vt_video_video_decode_accelerator_mac.*, which is now dead.

entry.title: [//media] Hardcode kDoNotAllocateGLTextures for video decoding on Mac
entry.content:
PictureBufferManager creates textures in CreatePictureBuffers() if the

passed-in `mode` specifies that it should allocate GL textures. This

`mode` argument is always false on Mac. This CL hardcodes this fact,

CHECK()-ing that `mode` is kDoNotAllocateGLTextures on Mac and

ifdef-ing out the code that creates GL textures.



This CL is the first step in eliminating the non-SharedImage case in

VtVideoDecodeAccelerator. See the linked bug for the full plan.

entry.title: base: Patch MessagePump tests
entry.content:
The MessagePump unit tests (in their Glib and Libevent variants) both

report a read of a stack address after its disappearance, centering on

the stack value `buf`. It appears that the task posted to the

`io_runner()` can run after control flow leaves the test body, which

would result in the no-longer-present stack address being dereferenced.



The remedy is to convert the stack-local into a fixture member.



For posterity, my repro was done with the following GN args:



```

symbol_level = 2

is_debug = false

is_asan = true

```

entry.title: Color pipeline: Fix old <link>s not getting deleted
entry.content:
There appears to be a race condition when onColorProviderChanged is

called multiple times in a row. Once the promise to load a new
